title: AeonMagnus .
desc:
When "The Transformers" (G1) originally aired, I used to tape each episode and watch it back several times that week until the next one aired. I kept them all, didn't tape over them. I liked to frame-advance thru the transformations to see what was going on.

When I had the figure, I'd check to see if they "got it right"; if I didn't, I'd watch to see how they worked. Of course, I was aware that they often cheated or just plain got it wrong, but it was cool to see them in action.

In keeping with "fair use", it's intended that these clips be a resource of analysis, comment and discourse about the Transformers phenomenon, and are therefore kept short and topical.

I also try to post a few unusual or unique items if I come across them, particularly things you might not have seen before or might not be common knowledge. So, don't be surprised if you find a few odd ones posted as well. I'm open to suggestions, but don't take it personally if I don't post your request.

P.S. No Spoilers.

title: TheBestAMVsOfAllTime
desc:
A collection of some of the best videos you will ever see. Sometimes may not upload for long periods of time, quality over quantity.

I upload to the 16 accounts in my subscription box or the link below primarily. "ineedacatchyname" and "NotGorz" are also mine. Playlists combine the videos from all channels.
Any other channel is a fake using my name.

I use multiple channels to post videos because policies on copyright on youtube could change at any time in the future for better or for worse. If the worst happened, for example: some record companies decided not to renew their contract with youtube, any channel with 100s of videos using copyrighted content would almost certainly be doomed regardless of "fair use". Where as I would survive having split all the videos up.

Use: http://tinyurl.com/BestAMVs

Everything on this channel is non-commercial and non-profit. I'm not a partner, no videos are monetized, I have no adsense account.
